Fiberglass of the kind used for insulation won't &quot;cut&quot; you,
but the fibers will make you itchy if you don't use gloves, etc.
The fibers are much larger than asbestos fibres and don't
pose the health threat that asbestos does.  But not clear
whether it is appropriate for your situation, anyway. (For
lack of details.)

<QUOTE PREVIOUSPOST="
&gt; Where could I even buy that?
">

Any home improvement store (&quot;Home Depot&quot;, et.al.) sells
at least a few different kinds of fiberglass insulation, typically
compressed into rolls that you can transport easily.  It is
commonly tinted pink and was advertised on TV using the
&quot;Pink Panther&quot; etc.  Some people hang it from their walls
and cover it with some kind of cloth (burlap, that cheap
doubleknit polyester, etc.) to control any escaping fibers.
