I can hear the groaning from this group even before I post this
reply.

Any sound deadening material is better than none.  The most obvious
reflections are the high frequency ones, and they are pretty easy to
cut back.  Thick blankets (packing blankets for instance) work pretty
well, as do simple acoustic tile, rugs etc.  It's best if you can hang
them a few inches from the walls.

These cheapo solutions aren't as good as you would like (try the rigid
fiberglass for better but more expensive treatment), but they will
help a good bit.  They don't absorb bass or even midrange - and that's
the stuff that will really wreak havoc with your recordings.

If you're handy, Ethan Winer has really great, simply built, and
inexpensive designs for real bass traps.  Search this site for his
previous posts.

Ken
