To add diffusion and remove boxiness without killing the reverb is
always the difficult trick with a small room. See if there is a shop
that sells carpet near you. The decent stuff comes on very heavy gauge
cardboard rolls a bit less than a foot in diameter, and you can
generally get old ones either free or very cheap. Cut some of these so
they will just stand upright in the room. Paint them some cool colour
and dot them around wherever you have space - you can always move them
later. They will do wonders for breaking up the room modes without
killing the space.

